<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<ecoSpold xmlns="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02" xmlns:xsi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema-instance" xsi:schemaLocation="http://www.EcoInvent.org/EcoSpold02 ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02.xsd http://www.EcoInvent.org/UsedUserMasterData ../../schemas/datasets/EcoSpold02UserMasterData.xsd">
  <childActivityDataset>
    <activityDescription>
      <activity specialActivityType="0" id="ea896826-ef62-5cc2-ac8d-23e32f80d823" activityNameId="669cd5b7-35bb-492b-8cb9-5dba90ed7890" parentActivityId="7395c931-1518-5634-b740-53b183e487b5" inheritanceDepth="-1" type="1">
        <activityName xml:lang="en">dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether production</activityName>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">Dipropylene glycol methyl ether</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">2-(2-METHOXYPROPOXY)-1-PROPANOL</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">CUDYYMUUJHLCGZ-UHFFFAOYSA-N</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">2-(2-methoxypropoxy)propan-1-ol</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">1-Propanol 2-(2-methoxypropoxy)-</synonym>
        <synonym xml:lang="en">13588-28-8</synonym>
        <includedActivitiesStart xml:lang="en">From the reception of propylene oxide and methanol at the factory gate.</includedActivitiesStart>
        <includedActivitiesEnd xml:lang="en">This activity ends with the production of dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether. It includes the processing of the input materials, consumption of energy, infrastructure use and emissions.</includedActivitiesEnd>
        <generalComment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether by the reaction of propylene oxide with methanol. Dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether is a colorless liquid with a mild pleasant odor. It is used as a solvent for coating systems, as an additive in paint removers, as a component in hydraulic fluids, and as starting material for the production of esters used as plasticizers. It reacts with acids to form esters, oxidizing agents to form aldehydes or carboxylic acids, alkali metals to form alcoholates or aldehydes to form acetals. These properties support the use of dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether in agricultural, cosmetic, electronic, ink, textile and adhesive products.</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">In this dataset, the raw materials are modelled with a stoechiometric calculation. The energy consumption, emissions and infrastructure are estimated based on data from a large chemical factory (Gendorf 2016).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Reference:</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="3">Gendorf (2016) Umwelterklärung 2015, Werk Gendorf Industriepark, www.gendorf.de.</text>
        </generalComment>
      </activity>
      <classification classificationId="28f738cc-bb73-48f8-b633-f83fb9bc5ddc">
        <classificationSystem xml:lang="en">ISIC rev.4 ecoinvent</classificationSystem>
        <classificationValue xml:lang="en">2011:Manufacture of basic chemicals</classificationValue>
      </classification>
      <geography geographyId="7846b897-7c04-4f9f-b607-2b83fcd9a74c">
        <shortname xml:lang="en">RoW</shortname>
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">The inventory is modelled for Europe but is assumed to be representative of the global production. Some values are based on data from a large chemical factory located in Germany. These are assumed to be valid for this geography.</text>
        </comment>
      </geography>
      <technology technologyLevel="3">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether is produced from the reaction of propylene oxide with methanol (etherification).</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="1">2 C3H6O + CH3OH → CH3(OC3H6)2OH</text>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="2">Kahlich, D., Wiechern, U., Lindner, J.: Propylene Oxide. Published online: 2000. In: Ullmann's Encyclopedia of Industrial Chemistry, Seventh Edition, 2004 Electronic Release (ed. Fiedler E., Grossmann G., Kersebohm D., Weiss G. and Witte C.). 7 th Electronic Release Edition. Wiley InterScience, New York, Online-Version under: http://www.mrw.interscience.wiley.com/emrw/9783527306732/home</text>
        </comment>
      </technology>
      <timePeriod startDate="2000-01-01" endDate="2023-12-31" isDataValidForEntirePeriod="true">
        <comment>
          <text xml:lang="en" index="0">Time of publications. Some values are based on data published by the Gendorf factory that were collected between 2011 and 2015. The time period has been adjusted accordingly. For more details, see the comments of the exchanges.</text>
        </comment>
      </timePeriod>
      <macroEconomicScenario macroEconomicScenarioId="d9f57f0a-a01f-42eb-a57b-8f18d6635801">
        <name xml:lang="en">Business-as-Usual</name>
      </macroEconomicScenario>
    </activityDescription>
    <flowData>
