        <productionVolumeComment xml:lang="en">Estimated value. The global production volume is extrapolated from the US production volume based on reports from Cefic (European Chemical Industry Council), and the American Chemistry Council.  
According to Cefic (2016) the Global sales of chemicals in the year 2015 was 3 534 billion euros. The reported share of sales per regions are: EU28 14.7%; Other Europe (Switzerland, Norway, Turkey, Russia and Ukraine) 2.7%; NAFTA (US, Canada and Mexico) 16.5%; Latin America 3.8%; China 39.9%; Japan 3.9%; Republic of Korea 3.2%; India 2.2%; Rest of Asia 11.9%; Rest of the World 1.3%. Cefic also reports the US total sales, 518.7 billion euros of the global 3 534 billion euros (14.7%). The same share is reported from the American Chemistry Council (2016), according to this source the USA sales account for 15% of global sales for the year 2016. 

According to the OECD the U.S. production volume of dipropylene glycol monomethyl ether for 2000 was 16 000 tonnes. The global value is scaled accordingly.

Reference(s):
Cefic 2016. Facts and figures 2016 of the European chemical industry. Accessible at: http://www.cefic.org/Facts-and-Figures/Chemicals-Industry-Profile/ 
American Chemistry Council 2016. Outlook: U.S. Chemical Industry Continues to Outpace Industrial Output; Accounts for More Than One-Half of Construction Spending by Manufacturing Sector. Accessible at: https://www.americanchemistry.com/Media/PressReleasesTranscripts/ACC-news-releases/US-Chemical-Industry-Continues-to-Outpace-Industrial-Output.html
OECD. 2001. Screening Information Dataset, Initial Assessment Profile for SIAM 12. Retrieved from: http://webnet.oecd.org/hpv/ui/handler.axd?id=82aa491f-c9e0-4b2f-81cf-e7ca3bceea1c, 15 June 2017.
</productionVolumeComment>
